AFTER A deliberately quiet few months, Presidential frontrunner Joe Biden seized the news cycle this week by announcing Senator Kamala Harris as his running mate. We hear about what she really stands for. And we ask what her time as California’s Attorney General tells us about how she would wield power in practice. John Prideaux, The Economist’s US editor, hosts with Charlotte Howard, New York bureau chief, and Washington correspondent Jon Fasman. Runtime: 34 min  Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn The podcast is complemented by our "Checks and Balance" newsletter. Sign up here. For access to The Economist’s print, digital and audio editions subscribe: economist.com/2020electionpod